The paper discusses the use of Artificial Neural Networks (ANNs) and their structural properties in predicting the performance of image classifiers. This falls under the category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper also discusses the potential advantages of Sparse Neural Networks, which could fall under the category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). The paper also uses techniques from Machine Learning (cs.LG), Computer Vision (cs.CV), and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) to analyze the structural properties of ANNs.
